Mama's here. That's it.

810
01:02:15,650 --> 01:02:17,300
That's good.

811
01:02:17,310 --> 01:02:19,010
Yes, you'll be safe.

812
01:02:19,350 --> 01:02:21,610
You'll open your mouth. Drink it down.

813
01:02:21,760 --> 01:02:25,020
Swallow it down. Mama's
here. It's okay, Judith.

814
01:02:26,330 --> 01:02:28,590
Mama's here. It's okay.

815
01:02:28,600 --> 01:02:29,710
Okay.

816
01:02:57,630 --> 01:02:58,890
Agnes.

817
01:02:59,990 --> 01:03:01,350
Agnes.

818
01:03:01,970 --> 01:03:04,630
You have done all that you can.

819
01:03:07,320 --> 01:03:09,660
I will not let her cross over.

820
01:03:22,820 --> 01:03:27,010
Grandmama, you had three
daughters that were taken.

821
01:03:30,970 --> 01:03:32,600
Were they...

822
01:03:34,550 --> 01:03:36,280
Were they like Judith?

823
01:03:39,360 --> 01:03:41,170
Anne was seven.

824
01:03:43,390 --> 01:03:45,770
The other two were just babies.

825
01:03:46,060 --> 01:03:48,760
They all had swellings and...

826
01:03:50,440 --> 01:03:52,750
...fever like Judith.

827
01:03:52,940 --> 01:03:55,370
Your mother's trying to...

828
01:03:55,520 --> 01:03:57,720
keep a grip on her child.

829
01:03:58,500 --> 01:04:00,370
It won't work.

830
01:04:03,620 --> 01:04:07,020
What is given may be
taken away at any time.

831
01:04:09,900 --> 01:04:12,470
We must never let our guard down.

832
01:04:13,720 --> 01:04:16,480
Never take for granted...

833
01:04:18,830 --> 01:04:21,290
...that our children's hearts beat,

834
01:04:21,310 --> 01:04:23,780
that they draw breath,

835
01:04:23,950 --> 01:04:27,580
that they walk and speak and...

836
01:04:30,290 --> 01:04:33,920
...smile, argue, play.

837
01:04:36,360 --> 01:04:40,340
Never forget for a moment
that they may be gone.

838
01:04:47,420 --> 01:04:49,320
Jude.

839
01:05:31,680 --> 01:05:32,970
Jude.

840
01:05:44,600 --> 01:05:46,470
Don't be sad.

841
01:05:48,740 --> 01:05:51,040
You shall be well.

842
01:05:51,800 --> 01:05:53,740
I shall not.

843
01:05:54,190 --> 01:05:56,370
Not without you.

844
01:06:08,520 --> 01:06:10,130
It's here.

845
01:06:10,140 --> 01:06:11,870
Do you see it, Jude?

846
01:06:18,430 --> 01:06:20,300
It's watching us.

847
01:06:21,750 --> 01:06:24,100
I'll tell it to take us both.

848
01:06:24,110 --> 01:06:25,930
We'll go together.

849
01:06:33,690 --> 01:06:35,590
Turn away.

850
01:06:36,080 --> 01:06:37,920
Turn away.

851
01:06:45,220 --> 01:06:47,140
It'll make a mistake.

852
01:06:48,420 --> 01:06:50,530
It can't tell us apart.

853
01:06:53,040 --> 01:06:55,250
Breathe with me, Judith.

854
01:07:27,200 --> 01:07:30,040
I give you my life.

855
01:07:30,190 --> 01:07:32,420
You shall be well.

856
01:07:32,550 --> 01:07:35,450
I give you my life, Judith.

857
01:07:41,680 --> 01:07:43,750
I'll be brave.

858
01:07:45,330 --> 01:07:47,790
I'll be brave, Father.

859
01:07:47,810 --> 01:07:49,610
I'll be brave.

860
01:07:52,300 --> 01:07:54,050
I'll be brave.

861
01:07:55,740 --> 01:07:57,480
I'll be brave, Father.

862
01:07:57,490 --> 01:07:59,160
I'll be brave.

863
01:08:01,660 --> 01:08:03,670
I'll be brave.

864
01:08:30,630 --> 01:08:31,630
Whoa.

865
01:08:33,760 --> 01:08:35,390
Quick as you can.

866
01:09:21,160 --> 01:09:22,810
Hamnet.

867
01:09:22,830 --> 01:09:24,190
Hamnet, you're not
supposed to be down here.

868
01:09:24,200 --> 01:09:25,910
I need to take you up to bed.

869
01:09:32,130 --> 01:09:33,570
Hamnet.

870
01:09:35,290 --> 01:09:36,890
Hamnet?

871
01:09:57,910 --> 01:09:59,550
Mama.

872
01:10:02,690 --> 01:10:04,290
Mama.

873
01:10:07,380 --> 01:10:08,950
Mama.

874
01:10:56,690 --> 01:10:58,450
Hamnet.

875
01:10:58,680 --> 01:11:00,480
You must open your mouth.

876
01:11:01,830 --> 01:11:03,150
All will be well.

877
01:11:13,850 --> 01:11:15,450
He's burning.

878
01:11:15,590 --> 01:11:16,990
He's burning up.

879
01:11:17,010 --> 01:11:19,090
It will not sti-- It will not stick!

880
01:11:21,200 --> 01:11:22,500
A stone. There's a stone.

881
01:11:22,510 --> 01:11:24,300
There's a stone upstairs
with a hole in the middle of it.

882
01:11:24,320 --> 01:11:26,340
By his bedside.
Bring it down. I need it.

883
01:11:26,350 --> 01:11:28,500
And, um, uh, salt. Get salt.

884
01:11:28,510 --> 01:11:29,780
Get it. Can you give it?

885
01:11:29,800 --> 01:11:32,430
Can you f-fetch me some
salt, as much salt as you have.

886
01:11:32,690 --> 01:11:34,360
Water. We need water.

887
01:11:34,370 --> 01:11:36,300
He's... he's too hot.

888
01:11:36,310 --> 01:11:37,830
He's burning.

889
01:11:37,840 --> 01:11:39,880
My love. Mama's here.

890
01:11:39,900 --> 01:11:41,790
All will be well. All will be well.

891
01:11:41,850 --> 01:11:43,510
All will be well.

892
01:11:46,860 --> 01:11:48,570
All will be well.

893
01:11:52,230 --> 01:11:55,520
Hamnet, don't be scared.

894
01:11:55,540 --> 01:11:57,130
No need to be scared.

895
01:11:57,150 --> 01:11:59,110
All will be well. Mommy's here.

896
01:11:59,130 --> 01:12:01,760
Mommy's here. It's okay.

897
01:12:01,810 --> 01:12:03,200
Mommy's here.

898
01:12:03,220 --> 01:12:05,000
Look at me. Mommy's here.

899
01:12:05,010 --> 01:12:07,840
I will never, ever let you go.

900
01:12:08,300 --> 01:12:09,170
You understand?

901
01:12:09,190 --> 01:12:11,980
I will never, ever let you go.

902
01:12:11,990 --> 01:12:13,590
I love you.

903
01:12:15,510 --> 01:12:16,810
I love you.

904
01:12:26,400 --> 01:12:29,600
Eliza, take Judith to the
kitchen and keep her there.

905
01:12:29,610 --> 01:12:30,980
Please!

906
01:12:32,940 --> 01:12:35,200
- He needs me!
- Stay there.

907
01:12:35,240 --> 01:12:37,570
He needs me!

908
01:12:37,630 --> 01:12:39,060
Please!

909
01:12:44,370 --> 01:12:46,060
Valerian...

910
01:12:47,600 --> 01:12:50,380
Hamnet. Hamnet. Hamnet.

911
01:12:50,390 --> 01:12:53,090
Hamnet, you have to
stay. Hamnet, please.

912
01:12:53,290 --> 01:12:55,290
Hamnet, please. You
have to stay with us.

913
01:12:55,300 --> 01:12:56,880
Mama needs you. We need you.

914
01:12:56,900 --> 01:12:59,090
- Stop! Enough!
- Stay with us. Stay, stay.

915
01:12:59,100 --> 01:13:00,520
Please, Hamnet. Hamnet, Hamnet, Hamnet.

916
01:13:00,530 --> 01:13:01,880
- Let him alone!
- Hamnet, please!

917
01:13:01,890 --> 01:13:04,990
Can't you see that
it's too late for him!

918
01:13:06,040 --> 01:13:08,340
Please, please.

919
01:13:08,390 --> 01:13:09,650
Hamnet?

920
01:13:09,820 --> 01:13:12,120
Hamnet. Hamnet. Please. Hamnet.

921
01:13:57,350 --> 01:13:59,650
My son is gone.

922
01:14:00,770 --> 01:14:03,250
Just so bereft... it's my son.

923
01:14:03,430 --> 01:14:05,060
I've lost my...

924
01:15:12,820 --> 01:15:15,030
I saw the light, and I couldn't sleep.

925
01:15:23,490 --> 01:15:25,200
Here.

926
01:15:45,140 --> 01:15:46,700
Oh, child, no.

927
01:15:46,720 --> 01:15:49,440
- No, no, no. Go to bed.
- No, no, let-let her stay.

928
01:15:53,080 --> 01:15:55,260
It is my fault, Mama. It is my fault.

929
01:15:55,280 --> 01:15:57,450
No. No.

930
01:15:58,200 --> 01:16:02,140
It is not your fault, Judith.

931
01:16:02,160 --> 01:16:04,170
But he changed places with me.

932
01:16:04,350 --> 01:16:05,740
He tricked it.

933
01:16:05,750 --> 01:16:07,200
He tricked what?

934
01:16:07,210 --> 01:16:08,440
Death.

935
01:16:08,830 --> 01:16:09,920
Judith.

936
01:16:09,940 --> 01:16:12,440
It took him when it came for me.

937
01:16:13,440 --> 01:16:16,180
Never say those words
to anyone ever again.

938
01:16:17,930 --> 01:16:20,830
The fever came for your
brother, and it took him.

939
01:16:21,880 --> 01:16:24,110
Do you wish to see him?

940
01:16:25,380 --> 01:16:26,750
Yes.

941
01:16:35,390 --> 01:16:37,390
Go on. You can see him.

942
01:16:49,270 --> 01:16:51,240
Is it really him?

943
01:16:52,770 --> 01:16:54,170
Yes.

944
01:16:56,790 --> 01:16:59,720
It-it doesn't look like him.

945
01:17:02,590 --> 01:17:03,930
No.

946
01:17:10,590 --> 01:17:12,720
It's not him.

947
01:17:13,250 --> 01:17:14,820
It's not.

948
01:17:16,060 --> 01:17:17,310
It's not him.

949
01:17:19,780 --> 01:17:21,490
It-It's-it's not morning yet.

950
01:17:21,510 --> 01:17:23,440
We haven't prepared him properly.

951
01:17:25,190 --> 01:17:27,120
Am I too late?

952
01:17:33,300 --> 01:17:34,430
- It's you.
- Father.

953
01:17:34,450 --> 01:17:35,690
It's you.

954
01:17:42,700 --> 01:17:44,030
It's me.

955
01:18:02,010 --> 01:18:03,640
Where is he?

956
01:18:06,520 --> 01:18:08,020
Where is...

957
01:18:12,530 --> 01:18:13,900
Where...

958
01:18:58,840 --> 01:19:01,130
It's my boy.

959
01:19:05,430 --> 01:19:07,400
It's my boy.

960
01:19:29,180 --> 01:19:31,150
I didn't see it.

961
01:19:38,190 --> 01:19:40,500
I should've paid him more attention.

962
01:19:40,520 --> 01:19:42,620
I always thought she was
the one to be taken away

963
01:19:42,640 --> 01:19:44,970
when all the while it was him.

964
01:19:46,060 --> 01:19:47,050
I'm a fool.

965
01:19:47,070 --> 01:19:49,940
No, there's nothing anyone
could have done to save him.

966
01:19:50,960 --> 01:19:52,690
You did everything that you could.

967
01:19:52,700 --> 01:19:54,440
Of course I did.

968
01:19:56,170 --> 01:19:57,790
You weren't here.

969
01:19:57,810 --> 01:19:59,580
I would have cut my heart
out and given it to him.

970
01:19:59,600 --> 01:20:01,430
I would have laid my life
down on the ground for him.

971
01:20:01,450 --> 01:20:03,340
- I-I know. I know.
- And no one would take it.

972
01:20:03,360 --> 01:20:05,950
- But you...
- No, you don't know.

973
01:20:06,130 --> 01:20:08,830
You don't know. You weren't here.

974
01:20:10,560 --> 01:20:12,200
He died in agony.

975
01:20:12,220 --> 01:20:13,590
I...

976
01:20:16,590 --> 01:20:18,510
- He was in agony.
- Agnes.

977
01:20:18,530 --> 01:20:20,060
He cried and he cried

978
01:20:20,070 --> 01:20:21,730
- and he cried and he cried.
- Agnes, stop, stop.

979
01:20:21,750 --> 01:20:23,330
- And his little body was wracked in pain.
- Shh.

980
01:20:23,340 --> 01:20:24,590
No, don't shush me.

981
01:20:24,600 --> 01:20:25,980
He was so scared.

982
01:20:26,000 --> 01:20:27,820
- And you weren't here.
- I know.

983
01:20:31,990 --> 01:20:33,810
I tried everything I could.

984
01:20:33,820 --> 01:20:35,410
I know you did.

985
01:20:35,550 --> 01:20:38,250
- I tried everything I could.
- You did everything that you could.

986
01:20:38,260 --> 01:20:40,980
You did everything that you could.

987
01:20:41,000 --> 01:20:42,560
Everything.

988
01:20:44,120 --> 01:20:46,540
Everything.

989
01:20:48,600 --> 01:20:51,110
Agnes. Agnes.

990
01:21:14,480 --> 01:21:16,440
I will send word, Agnes.

991
01:21:16,460 --> 01:21:18,700
You'll send word?

992
01:21:19,020 --> 01:21:21,250
- To whom?
- To you.

993
01:21:28,860 --> 01:21:30,820
I'm here.

994
01:21:31,980 --> 01:21:34,540
What I meant was that I shall
send word when I reach London.

995
01:21:34,550 --> 01:21:36,180
London?

996
01:21:37,710 --> 01:21:39,510
I must leave.

997
01:21:42,810 --> 01:21:44,590
Leave? How can you leave?

998
01:21:44,600 --> 01:21:47,940
The world does simply
not stand still, Agnes.

999
01:21:51,020 --> 01:21:53,010
There are people
waiting for me in London.

1000
01:21:53,410 --> 01:21:54,760
The season is about to begin,

1001
01:21:54,770 --> 01:21:57,860
and my company shall
return from Kent any day now.

1002
01:22:03,560 --> 01:22:06,110
I have to go now.

1003
01:22:06,120 --> 01:22:07,690
Now?

1004
01:22:08,310 --> 01:22:10,000
There's a traveling
party leaving today,

1005
01:22:10,010 --> 01:22:12,810
and they have a spare horse, so yeah.

1006
01:22:14,640 --> 01:22:16,620
Look after the girls,
and I will return to--

1007
01:22:16,640 --> 01:22:18,000
Stop.

1008
01:22:18,770 --> 01:22:20,990
Don't.

1009
01:22:48,540 --> 01:22:50,660
Go. Go.

1010
01:23:02,840 --> 01:23:06,490
"When I do count the
clock that tells the time,

1011
01:23:06,510 --> 01:23:10,370
"And see the brave day
sunk in hideous night;

1012
01:23:10,390 --> 01:23:13,860
"When I behold the violet past prime,

1013
01:23:13,870 --> 01:23:17,930
"And sable curls all
silver'd o'er with white;

1014
01:23:17,940 --> 01:23:22,020
"When lofty trees I
see barren of leaves

1015
01:23:22,030 --> 01:23:25,830
"Which erst from the
heat did canopy the herd,

1016
01:23:25,840 --> 01:23:29,960
"And summer's green
all girded up in sheaves

1017
01:23:29,970 --> 01:23:34,840
"Borne on the bier with
white and bristly beard;

1018
01:23:34,860 --> 01:23:38,350
"Then of thy beauty do I question make,

1019
01:23:38,360 --> 01:23:41,330
"Thou among the wastes of time must go,

1020
01:23:41,340 --> 01:23:45,140
"Since sweets and beauties
do themselves forsake

1021
01:23:45,150 --> 01:23:48,420
"And die as fast as
they see others grow;

1022
01:23:48,430 --> 01:23:51,530
"And nothing gainst time's
scythe can make defense

1023
01:23:51,540 --> 01:23:55,900
Save breed, to brave him
when he takes thee hence."

1024
01:23:56,970 --> 01:23:58,980
Will you read it again?

1025
01:23:59,320 --> 01:24:00,890
No.

1026
01:24:00,950 --> 01:24:02,960
I've read it three times.

1027
01:24:04,010 --> 01:24:05,760
That's enough.

1028
01:24:09,010 --> 01:24:11,600
- Shall we do presents?
- Presents? from London?

1029
01:24:11,620 --> 01:24:13,630
A hair comb for you, Jude.

1030
01:24:15,840 --> 01:24:17,870
Mind you, you'll have to be careful.

1031
01:24:24,280 --> 01:24:26,000
This is for you, Agnes.

1032
01:24:35,360 --> 01:24:38,010
- A ruby, is it?
- Mm-hmm.

1033
01:24:38,030 --> 01:24:40,720
It's the finest I've ever seen.

1034
01:24:41,280 --> 01:24:43,810
Everyone's talking about the new house.

1035
01:24:43,830 --> 01:24:45,670
It's the biggest in Stratford.

1036
01:24:45,680 --> 01:24:48,560
There are so many
rooms. One could get lost.

1037
01:24:48,570 --> 01:24:50,930
You shall keep the keys, Susanna.

1038
01:24:50,950 --> 01:24:53,150
You shall manage the house well.

1039
01:24:54,860 --> 01:24:56,500
Put it on, Mama.

1040
01:25:16,410 --> 01:25:19,700
Did Bartholomew show you the new house?

1041
01:25:19,710 --> 01:25:21,140
Mm-hmm.

1042
01:25:23,270 --> 01:25:24,970
Do you like it?

1043
01:25:26,530 --> 01:25:28,760
Why didn't you show me yourself?

1044
01:25:30,380 --> 01:25:32,920
Were you afraid I wouldn't leave?

1045
01:25:34,650 --> 01:25:37,180
'Cause Hamnet died here in this house.

1046
01:25:46,130 --> 01:25:48,670
You know, I'm constantly
wondering where he is.

1047
01:25:50,380 --> 01:25:52,390
Or where he has gone.

1048
01:25:55,020 --> 01:25:58,850
Whatever I'm doing, I'm
wondering, "Where is he?"

1049
01:25:59,730 --> 01:26:02,060
I mean, he can't have just vanished.

1050
01:26:04,760 --> 01:26:06,760
All he needs is for me to find him.

1051
01:26:06,780 --> 01:26:09,250
He must be somewhere.

1052
01:26:10,360 --> 01:26:14,230
I fear I may run mad with
it, even now, a year on.

1053
01:26:14,350 --> 01:26:16,250
A year is nothing.

1054
01:26:20,460 --> 01:26:24,320
A year is nothing. It's every second...

1055
01:26:24,420 --> 01:26:26,590
every minute, every day.

1056
01:26:29,040 --> 01:26:32,270
We may never stop looking for him.

1057
01:26:33,770 --> 01:26:35,810
I'm sorry, Agnes.

1058
01:26:38,800 --> 01:26:40,200
Did you hear me? I
said that I'm sorry, Agnes.

1059
01:26:40,210 --> 01:26:41,490
- For what?
- For everything.

1060
01:26:41,500 --> 01:26:43,000
- You're caught by that place.
- For...

1061
01:26:43,020 --> 01:26:44,930
- What place?
- That place in your head.

1062
01:26:44,950 --> 01:26:46,610
It is now more real to
you than anywhere else.

1063
01:26:46,620 --> 01:26:50,510
Not even the death of our
child can keep you from it.

1064
01:26:51,970 --> 01:26:54,100
Hamnet died.

1065
01:26:54,290 --> 01:26:56,090
A horrible death.

1066
01:26:57,460 --> 01:26:59,630
And you should have been there.

1067
01:27:00,780 --> 01:27:02,820
You could have bid him farewell.

1068
01:27:32,670 --> 01:27:34,710
What do you see?

1069
01:27:36,050 --> 01:27:37,490
Hmm?

1070
01:27:41,950 --> 01:27:43,520
Nothing.

1071
01:27:48,220 --> 01:27:49,820
Nothing?

1072
01:27:51,980 --> 01:27:53,850
Nothing at all.

1073
01:27:53,950 --> 01:27:55,630
Oh, well.

1074
01:28:00,380 --> 01:28:02,680
You should go back to London.

1075
01:28:04,740 --> 01:28:08,070
You need not concern yourself with us.

1076
01:28:09,370 --> 01:28:12,240
Get along just fine without you.

1077
01:28:15,190 --> 01:28:17,370
This was sometime a paradox,

1078
01:28:17,380 --> 01:28:20,320
